Aphotic.name: Aphotic
Aphotic.addedLore: This dark relic was found at the very bottom of the deepest trench of the ocean. It drains all light surrounding it, blinding everything in a strange abyssal darkness.

Aries.name: Aries
Aries.addedLore: Two iron horns adorn this helmet to enhance the warriors of the Eradian, Dwarves who specifically rode Rams into battle at incredible speed.

Blue Mask.name: Blue Mask
Blue Mask.addedLore: The Blue Mask's physical traits are equal to that of paper, but the mystical properties enhance the wearers personal skills tenfold. The mask is thought to originate from an ancient Dernel tribe.

Bovine Killer.name: Bovine Killer
Bovine Killer.addedLore: This helmet was worn long ago by an infamous assassin who plagued Bovemist sites for decades. It was crafted of the still-bloody skin of their most prized and worshiped cows.

Call of the Void.name: Call of the Void
Call of the Void.addedLore: Originating from the unspeakable dark land, looking into the helmet will show nothing but darkness. Wearing it is said to reverse your morality, as if it were draining your will to live into the void.

Conflagrate.name: Conflagrate
Conflagrate.addedLore: Donning this helmet sears your mind with images of a world on fire. These blistering thoughts pressure you to make that world a reality.

Butterfly.name: Butterfly
Butterfly.addedLore: "Time travel cares less about small things like a flapping wing, and more about big things, like becoming your own grandfather." -Martyn, Time Valley Resident

Brise.name: Brise
Brise.addedLore: "With the hot, dry winds from the Roots and the cold, wet winds from Nesaak, these houses rot faster than you can blink." -Viraex, Elkurn Citizen

Gale's Sight.name: Gale's Sight
Gale's Sight.addedLore: True to their promise, these goggles were left as a memento for Ohms when his lover Gale finally died. Light as air, Gale's carefree nature lends itself to those who don them.

Dune Beast Jaw.name: Dune Beast Jaw
Dune Beast Jaw.addedLore: "We're trying to dig up history, not horrors! What is wrong with this province?!"  -Excavator Vade, WynnExcavation Site A Director

Cephalothorax.name: Cephalothorax
Cephalothorax.addedLore: "...Most of their vital organs, however, are located in the bulbous abdomen. If you've enough crushing force with your weapon, it may be a quicker alternative for the kill. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

Black Ripper.name: Black Ripper
Black Ripper.addedLore: "The skeletons at Ancient Nemract are rotted! is it even physically possible to rot a bone?" -Laen, Nemract Librarian

Fenmask.name: Fenmask
Fenmask.addedLore: This matted tangle of vines and marshland plants contains various herbal remedies woven into it. It is oddly comfortable, despite the thorns coating the inside.

Grillface.name: Grillface
Grillface.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] The old facemasks of the Eradian guards were forged from raw magma, and enchanted to remain searingly hot, so as to brand the wearer eternally with the mark of Rodoroc's elite.

Anima-Infused Helmet.name: Anima-Infused Helmet
Anima-Infused Helmet.addedLore: Engraved with the beauty and mystery of the boreal lights, this ornately-crafted crown is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Obsidian-Framed Helmet.name: Obsidian-Framed Helmet
Obsidian-Framed Helmet.addedLore: Made of dark minerals and adorned with pure obsidian, this ornately-crafted helmet is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Heliophilia.name: Heliophilia
Heliophilia.addedLore: This peculiar shawl is eternally warm to the touch, and shimmers brilliantly in the sunlight. It is rumored to give amazing health benefits and good fortune to those who wear it.

Little Inferno.name: Little Inferno
Little Inferno.addedLore: It is cold to the touch until worn. Once donned, it engulfs the wearer in excruciatingly hot flames, but never shall the wearer burn; only their enemies will feel the pain of the fire.

Mask of the Spirits.name: Mask of the Spirits
Mask of the Spirits.addedLore: Not all who roam may find their way home. Others lose themselves in the world... And find a new way forward.

Blood Moon.name: Blood Moon
Blood Moon.addedLore: Imbued with the blood of the first werewolf, it was kept in Gelibord as a trophy before being stolen. Wearing it is said to mimic the effects of the lycanthropic curse.

Clearsight Spectacles.name: Clearsight Spectacles
Clearsight Spectacles.addedLore: Ancient magicks are required to make these brilliant glasses, imbued with charity and selflessness. They allow sight beyond sight, rumoured to allow sight of a brilliant realm.
Clearsight Spectacles.quest: Realm of Light IV - Finding the Light

Phoenix Prince's Crown.name: Phoenix Prince's Crown
Phoenix Prince's Crown.addedLore: The Phoenix Prince is a mythical figure spoken of in Avos legend. His crown cursed him in an endless cycle of death and rebirth.

Cancer.name: Cancer
Cancer.addedLore: 450 years ago a demonic plague like no other spread through Gavel, killing thousands. That is, until a priest encased the disease inside a helmet and warned everyone never to wear it.

Neolithic.name: Neolithic
Neolithic.addedLore: This ancient stone-hewn helmet is blended with the bones of an extinct animal of some kind. It is harder than dragon's hide.

Outrage.name: Outrage
Outrage.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] This battered stone mask is of unknown origin, and has no openings for the eyes whatsoever. Indeed, all that can be seen while wearing it is that which makes you truly angry.

Pelier.name: Pelier
Pelier.addedLore: Occasional whisperings can be heard by the wearers of this stone mask, reforged from a phylactery of souls. Although not dangerous, staring into the eyes of the mask can bring fear of one's soul being trapped within.

Pisces.name: Pisces
Pisces.addedLore: The oddly uncomfortable helmet was hand sculpted from a mystic clay found only in the depths of Molten Heights. Not much is known about the substance.

Scarlet Veil.name: Scarlet Veil
Scarlet Veil.addedLore: You're seeing red... Time to see more of it.

Shawl of Gaea.name: Shawl of Gaea
Shawl of Gaea.addedLore: Despite being thin enough to blow away in the wind, this mineral-blended shawl holds the force of a supervolcano within its soft fabric.

Shinespark.name: Shinespark
Shinespark.addedLore: There have been many attempts to create a reliable power system in Llevigar, and this plasma-charged helmet was reforged from a notable prototype.

Spectre.name: Spectre
Spectre.addedLore: The dark spectres of the decayed forests have created an insidious helmet to drain the spirit of those who wear it, and become servants to their dark whims. Many have fallen to its allure.

The Berserker's Helm.name: The Berserker's Helm
The Berserker's Helm.addedLore: Worn by a terrible berserker during his fanatical rampage through the land, his rage permeates this horned blackiron helmet.

The Forgery.name: The Forgery
The Forgery.addedLore: While only a mockery of the original product, this line of helmets became wildly popular before legal disputes and safety concerns halted production.

Third Eye.name: Third Eye
Third Eye.addedLore: The Bantisu monks have developed this enigmatic sigil in their years of meditation and study. It blesses the wearer with luck and powerful psionic ability.

Venison.name: Venison
Venison.addedLore: This ancient Elven sacrificial mask contains only a sliver of its previous magic, yet the blessing of the Elven god Entia still greatly empowers those who don it.

Dondasch.name: Dondasch
Dondasch.addedLore: The sheer bond between Adamastor and Urdar has manifested itself into a physical form due to their duress. Such power is not to be abused...

Marius' Prison.name: Marius' Prison
Marius' Prison.addedLore: "I know the Beast may return one day...but these chains shall bind it for eternity." The inscription glows bright in the darkness.

Adamantite.name: Adamantite
Adamantite.addedLore: Adamantite is a soft metal often added to exotic medicine to increase one's health, but a revolutionary blacksmith on Black Road, created a chestplate with an Adamantite alloy, which is advertised to bolster the users endurance.

Andesite Aegis.name: Andesite Aegis
Andesite Aegis.addedLore: Andesite is a stone commonly used for weapons and construction, but tends to be ineffective as armor when impure. This sturdy chestplate, however, is testament to the strength of pure andesite.

Aquarius.name: Aquarius
Aquarius.addedLore: “The symbol of the river” is a name that is often synonymous with this garment, with many water like qualities surrounding it, heavily bathed in magical meaning.

Blessed Wrappings.name: Blessed Wrappings
Blessed Wrappings.addedLore: The thick, Bovemist-sanctified cloth is worn by their priests during certain religious ceremonies. It clears the mind and purifies the body.

Booster Plate.name: Booster Plate
Booster Plate.addedLore: A marvel of Corkus' electromagical advancements, this high-tech chestplate is equipped with steam jets to boost the user's speed, at a minimal cost to protection.

Cage of Bones.name: Cage of Bones
Cage of Bones.addedLore: The ancient bones of the demon Garaheth are stronger than steel. They clamp down when worn to constrict the bearer, inciting a slow madness.

Cardiac Arrest.name: Cardiac Arrest
Cardiac Arrest.addedLore: ...As the heart fails, adrenaline pumps through the body in an attempt to provide energy and keep the victim alive, but medical action must be taken to ensure survival. -Excerpt from Aldorei Medical Tomes, Vol. 6

Chimaera.name: Chimaera
Chimaera.addedLore: The one true Chimera in existence is sought by many, for great stories are told of its gifts to the worthy. One such gift was a simple fur coat, which gave the wearer but a taste of its power.

Garoth's Hope.name: Garoth's Hope
Garoth's Hope.addedLore: "Strangest thing, it turns out Creepers are incredibly flammable..." -Garull, Cryptid Researcher

Tisaun's Valor.name: Tisaun's Valor
Tisaun's Valor.addedLore: Tisaun, a warrior tasked to fend off a corrupted siege alone, could find only a thin shirt and rusted spear to use before the attack. He defeated all 1000 enemies without taking a scratch, and his bravery infused his gear with that same strength.

Arakadicus' Body.name: Arakadicus' Body
Arakadicus' Body.addedLore: Long strips of chitin discarded from the mother of spiders Arakadicus still contain traces of her wicked powers, but few have survived the attempts to harvest them.

Springtrap.name: Springtrap
Springtrap.addedLore: "After nearly getting trapped in an iron maiden, I figure I can study  those mummies just as well from home." -Achper, Almuj Archaeologist

Ribcage.name: Ribcage
Ribcage.addedLore: "...as intimidating as the name sounds, you want your organs to be trapped in this kind of cage." -Excerpt from Human Anatomy For Fools, Cirh Nettan

Abdomen.name: Abdomen
Abdomen.addedLore: "...But under no circumstances should you stand directly behind an attacking spider. While not a universal trait, some spiders are capable of ejecting webs from their spinneret, leaving assailants and victims helpless." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

Web Plate.name: Web Plate
Web Plate.addedLore: "I just need a little more spider silk to finish this vest!" -Lacrona, Detlas Tailor, found eaten by Nivla spiders

Dead Samurai's Plate.name: Dead Samurai's Plate
Dead Samurai's Plate.addedLore: "We get a lot of weirdos coming from Gavel by airship. That plate mail looked unusably ornate!" -Calo, Private Airship Operator

Erratio.name: Erratio
Erratio.addedLore: The blind prophet who crafted this macabre breastplate used the bones of only the most ruthless justiciars and executioners. Its wearers are supposedly destined to only die either a heroic or a just death.

Giant's Bracer.name: Giant's Bracer
Giant's Bracer.addedLore: This ill-fitting, bulky chestplate was never intended to be a chestplate at all. Rather, it is a broken fragment of an arm bracer, from the time of giants.

Gravity.name: Gravity
Gravity.addedLore: No one knows how this extremely dense chestplate can even logically exist. It is almost paradoxical in nature, and affects its wearers in unfathomable ways.

Boreal-Patterned Aegis.name: Boreal-Patterned Aegis
Boreal-Patterned Aegis.addedLore: Infused with the classical magicks of fire, water, and thunder, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Elysium-Engraved Aegis.name: Elysium-Engraved Aegis
Elysium-Engraved Aegis.addedLore: Dedicated to a place of courage revered by all warriors, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Twilight-Gilded Cloak.name: Twilight-Gilded Cloak
Twilight-Gilded Cloak.addedLore: An ephemeral moment in time captured by sheer force of magic, this ornately-crafted cloak is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Hetusol.name: Hetusol
Hetusol.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] The make of this massive cloak is unlike anything seen before among the provinces. Foreign images shift and melt in ethereal projections within the inside.

Katoa's Warmth.name: Katoa's Warmth
Katoa's Warmth.addedLore: Brilliantly golden as the crops from the humble farm, its mere presence fills stomachs and brings comfort, but only to those who are modest and generous.

Leo.name: Leo
Leo.addedLore: This thick skinned jacket, imbued with the courage of a thousand lion hearts, will grant the user massive protection from all who target them.

Libra.name: Libra
Libra.addedLore: Before the invention of magical weight detectors, there was a giant pair of public scales in Cinfras. Instead of being thrown away, they were reforged to be a formidable piece of armour.

Discoverer.name: Discoverer
Discoverer.addedLore: Wealth and riches...but at what cost?

Matryoshka Shell.name: Matryoshka Shell
Matryoshka Shell.addedLore: The armor worn by the enigmatic Matryoshka Idol. It appears to have a nearly uncountably high number of inlets and sockets set inside.

Millennium.name: Millennium
Millennium.addedLore: Cosmic energy permeates this deceptively dull-looking chestplate, having been crafted with stardust from a comet that only passes over Wynn every 1000 years.

Blue Wynnter Sweater.name: Blue Wynnter Sweater
Blue Wynnter Sweater.addedLore: The sweater has the quote "Don't feel BLUE- It's Craftmas!" knitted onto the front.

Bob's Battle Chestplate.name: Bob's Battle Chestplate
Bob's Battle Chestplate.addedLore: This battered chestplate was once worn by the legendary Wynnic protector, Bob, during the fearsome corrupted sieges before he gave it away to an old friend. An air of melancholy hangs over it.

Cloak of Luminosity.name: Cloak of Luminosity
Cloak of Luminosity.quest: Realm of Light III - A Headless History

Green Wynnter Sweater.name: Green Wynnter Sweater
Green Wynnter Sweater.addedLore: The sweater has the quote "I'm feeling PINE, what about you" knitted onto the front.

Mummy's Rag.name: Mummy's Rag
Mummy's Rag.addedLore: The accursed mummy once wore this robe as a great pharaoh of the desert. It has long since rotted, leaving only a cursed shell of its former greatness.

Inhibitor.name: Inhibitor
Inhibitor.addedLore: There's a note in it. It doesn't seem to be addressed to you...  "You're not beyond saving. But you must work to deserve to be saved."

Purple Wynnter Sweater.name: Purple Wynnter Sweater
Purple Wynnter Sweater.addedLore: The sweater has the quote "ICY you looking at my fancy duds" knitted onto the front.

Red Wynnter Sweater.name: Red Wynnter Sweater
Red Wynnter Sweater.addedLore: The sweater has the quote "I'll never give you the COLD SHOULDER" knitted onto the front.

White Wynnter Sweater.name: White Wynnter Sweater
White Wynnter Sweater.addedLore: The sweater has the quote "SNOW way Craftmas can be bad in this sweater" knitted onto the front.

Nemract's Ruin.name: Nemract's Ruin
Nemract's Ruin.addedLore: This chestplate was originally created as a memorial ornament to the lost lives of Ancient Nemract before being reforged into a powerful piece of armor for Nemract's guard.

Ragni's Mail.name: Ragni's Mail
Ragni's Mail.addedLore: One of the few remaining standard issue mails that were used against the first hordes to emerge from the infamous portal over 1000 years ago.

Cinfras Souvenir T-Shirt.name: Cinfras Souvenir T-Shirt
Cinfras Souvenir T-Shirt.addedLore: The shirt has the quote "I went to the Letvus Airbase in Cinfras and all I got was this lousy T-shirt" printed on it.

Enhanced Copper Plate.name: Enhanced Copper Plate
Enhanced Copper Plate.addedLore: The merchant insists that the wear and oxidation on the armor "is a feature."

Sawdust.name: Sawdust
Sawdust.addedLore: Once cursed by a druid who had his grove chopped away by a greedy Villager, it was then purified and mass-produced for sale as armor, to the druid's utter disappointment.

Taurus.name: Taurus
Taurus.addedLore: The hide of the Touroto, an almost invincible Bull-like creature, is said to be pierced only by the horn of the Touroto itself, making it extremely valuable.

The Jingling Jester.name: The Jingling Jester
The Jingling Jester.addedLore: Jingle jangle, while shaking your bells. Jingle jangle come the pockets of cash... Catch the trickster, send them to hell," their money is gone and off you've dashed!

Time Rift.name: Time Rift
Time Rift.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] You only have limited time. But what if, you could experience that time again? And again, and again...

Alternator.name: Alternator
Alternator.addedLore: Llevigar's schools of wizardry are notorious for their difficult training regimens. These leg plates, forcing users to balance spellcasting with direct combat, are often cited as the tipping point for successful wizards.

Asphyxia.name: Asphyxia
Asphyxia.addedLore: A condition of severely deficient supply of oxygen to the body that arises from abnormal breathing; practitioners that abuse specific magic combos are often found incapacitated by said condition.

Bridge of the Divide.name: Bridge of the Divide
Bridge of the Divide.addedLore: These leggings hold the interest of many researching the corruption, as they are the only documented case of a non-corrupt fusion of dark and light energy, made of pure twilight.

Chained Pixels.name: Chained Pixels
Chained Pixels.addedLore: Materials of all sorts have been lashed together in this crude, blocky set of leggings. From darksteel to leather to rotting wood, each part is a perfect square. It has, so far, been impossible to recreate.

Conductor.name: Conductor
Conductor.addedLore: Using an unorthodox method of smithing, these copper leggings are insulated with an extremely conductive blend of liquid to improve electrical discharge.

Conspirator's Trickpockets.name: Conspirator's Trickpockets
Conspirator's Trickpockets.addedLore: No reign lasts forever. Not while your schemes remain unnoticed.

Crystal.name: Crystal
Crystal.addedLore: Forged on Mage Island, the sparkling liquid-like armour is as hard as obsidian, but light and fluid as water. It glistens with the magic of the ocean winds.

Gold Digger.name: Gold Digger
Gold Digger.addedLore: "With the corruption seemingly tied to the emeralds dug by the Roots, people thought gold was the next best thing, the idiots." -Gerald, Retired Miner

Ohms' Rage.name: Ohms' Rage
Ohms' Rage.addedLore: These ancient, spark-coursing greaves are all that remains of the great thunder mage Ohms' favorite golem familiar after a dark force turned it against its masters.

Knee.name: Knee
Knee.addedLore: "I thought aiming for the legs would disable the enemy. Turns out they can drag themselves with their arms just as quick." -Therck, Ragni Soldier 3rd Division

Spinneret.name: Spinneret
Spinneret.addedLore: "...Spiders have a weak point in the cephalothorax, essentially the neck. A small target, but it isn't as tough to chop through as the rest of them. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

Dark Shroud.name: Dark Shroud
Dark Shroud.addedLore: Wearing this deceptively simple shroud causes the user to fade into the shadows, sometimes flickering out of existence for a moment.

Darkiron Scrap.name: Darkiron Scrap
Darkiron Scrap.addedLore: Despite being only an impure scrap of the normally sturdy blackiron, these heavy leggings still have extreme defensive capabilities.

Dead Sands.name: Dead Sands
Dead Sands.addedLore: Found in the middle of the Almuj desert, these greaves seem to slowly poison all life around them. Theorists suggest they were the handiwork of a wicked necromancer, though the truth is not known.

Gemini.name: Gemini
Gemini.addedLore: The gods of air and thunder, frustrated with being physically insubstantial alone, decided to band together to forge the ultimate leggings of defense.

Greaves of the Veneer.name: Greaves of the Veneer
Greaves of the Veneer.addedLore: Forged from mystic, previously unknown metals revealed in the deepest dwarven mining site to date, these sleek, glowing greaves are believed to be utterly indestructible.

Abyss-Imbued Leggings.name: Abyss-Imbued Leggings
Abyss-Imbued Leggings.addedLore: Steeped in the deepest energies of the Ahms region void, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Chaos-Woven Greaves.name: Chaos-Woven Greaves
Chaos-Woven Greaves.addedLore: With threads of fundamentally opposing magic delicately woven together, these ornately-crafted greaves are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Hephaestus-Forged Greaves.name: Hephaestus-Forged Greaves
Hephaestus-Forged Greaves.addedLore: Consecrated by Qira herself with blessings unknown to all but her, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Holy Greaves.name: Holy Greaves
Holy Greaves.addedLore: Many blacksmiths have tried to craft their products in this armor's image, but none so far have been able to capture the brilliance of these Bovemist-blessed greaves.

Impact Winter.name: Impact Winter
Impact Winter.addedLore: Do you think you can survive with a sky choked by snow and ash? More importantly, do you think anything else can?

Infernal Impulse.name: Infernal Impulse
Infernal Impulse.addedLore: If the depths of hell allows you this, is staying human an equal trade or a fool's choice?

Kelight's Shield.name: Kelight's Shield
Kelight's Shield.addedLore: Used by the Temple of the Legends' strongest guard, the shielded plating is enchanted with a powerful ward to stave off the effects of the corruption.

Kratke.name: Kratke
Kratke.addedLore: Spurred on by a drunken bet, the great Thanos smith Kratke improved a pair of leggings from a rival that were once thought to be perfection.

Lemon Legs.name: Lemon Legs
Lemon Legs.addedLore: Due to an unfortunate accident where he choked on a lemon, an unremarkable mercenary became a laughing stock. He later managed to shed the title, as he left no one alive who remembered the name.

Opulenity.name: Opulenity
Opulenity.addedLore: Made of an uncommonly used fabric called denim, these fashionable leggings exude style and elegance. Surely wearing them would bring you luck?

Philosopher.name: Philosopher
Philosopher.addedLore: What better excuse is there to sit in the shade and think about life?

Post-Ultima.name: Post-Ultima
Post-Ultima.addedLore: These leggings are the last remaining piece of a historical set of armor, created with such power as to be thought impossible long ago.

Enhanced DuskShield.name: Enhanced DuskShield
Enhanced DuskShield.addedLore: They look extremely bulky and uncomfortable...do they have a right to call it "enhanced"?

Enhanced Pickpockets.name: Enhanced Pickpockets
Enhanced Pickpockets.addedLore: Aside from the added plating, they look more or less intact. Somehow, that doesn't surprise you.

Sagittarius.name: Sagittarius
Sagittarius.addedLore: The hide of the centaur is extraordinarily magical in the right hands. It is told to allow the user to gain the swiftness of the horse, but also leaves them vulnerable to hard hitting attacks.

Vaward.name: Vaward
Vaward.addedLore: A once-great hero left behind these sturdy, reliable greaves, trusting those after her to be able to use their power to protect others, should they don them. Her courage fuels their wearers.

Winter's Essence.name: Winter's Essence
Winter's Essence.addedLore: These pure, snow-white leggings are rumored to have been crafted by the legendary ice mage Theorick. The people of Nesaak view them as cursed, seeking to destroy them in a bid to stop the endless winter surrounding them.

Phage Pins.name: Phage Pins
Phage Pins.addedLore: Salvaged from the limbs of the Vulcor Adrenophage, they radiate extreme heat,  suffusing the body they attach to with that same heat. It almost feels as though your blood is heating to a frenetic boil.

Almuj's Walker.name: Almuj's Walker
Almuj's Walker.addedLore: There used to be a constant battle between Almuj's thieves over these feather-light, gold-plated boots, until one day they were stolen by an unknown pickpocket and never seen again.

Anchoryl.name: Anchoryl
Anchoryl.addedLore: Despite being a much smaller settlement compared to the mighty citadel of Rodoroc, the dwarven smiths of Thanos still can forge mighty products, such as these heavy diamond-alloy boots.

Audacity.name: Audacity
Audacity.addedLore: A powerful mental curse surrounds these boots, inciting uncontrollable rage into the wearers, as well as the power to enact it upon others.

Bad Wolf.name: Bad Wolf
Bad Wolf.addedLore: The runic message carved on these enigmatic boots cover hundreds of different languages, many of them disused, but what has been translated seems to describe a disaster soon to arrive to the world.

Broken Balance.name: Broken Balance
Broken Balance.addedLore: Torn scraps of metal line the inside of these boots. They provide no protection, instead forcing a constant adrenaline rush while worn.

Capricorn.name: Capricorn
Capricorn.addedLore: During a spiritual journey to Kato temple, the sage Capian was presented with powerful spiritual boots with the intention to be used for peaceful magic, and not hard combat.

Cyclo.name: Cyclo
Cyclo.addedLore: A centuries-old storm spirit was banished to these tight boots for his destructive actions. His fury empowers those who wear them with the great force of a raging cyclone.

Mud.name: Mud
Mud.addedLore: "Some pigmen snuffle through dirt for things to eat. We dig up that soil to plant our crops in; it's always full of life." -Thomas, Ravine Village Resident

Cerid's Ingenuity.name: Cerid's Ingenuity
Cerid's Ingenuity.addedLore: One of the master tinkerer Cerid's greatest inventions, these odd gear-laced boots clink and chime with the sound of clockworks keeping its powerful magic dynamos constantly running.

Stingy.name: Stingy
Stingy.addedLore: "You should see when the spiders fight over a meal. It looks ridiculous, legs flailing everywhere!" -Captain Enduyn, Ragni Legion 1st Division

Disco.name: Disco
Disco.addedLore: Recovered from a corrupted soldier who wore them, it was found dancing instead of attacking those around it. Even after it was killed, it jostled and jerked around like a dancing puppet.

Giant Step.name: Giant Step
Giant Step.addedLore: Found in a mystically-charged Giant ruin, these snug boots recall fond memories, incite calmness, and provide comfort for the wearer.

Gaea-Hewn Boots.name: Gaea-Hewn Boots
Gaea-Hewn Boots.addedLore: Forged in direct tribute to the earth and its aspects, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Hephaestus-Forged Sabatons.name: Hephaestus-Forged Sabatons
Hephaestus-Forged Sabatons.addedLore: Honoring a mythical dwarven smith lost to the legends, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

Hunger.name: Hunger
Hunger.addedLore: Forgotten long ago, these boots curse the wearer with an endless hunger.

Boreal.name: Boreal
Boreal.addedLore: The last known crafts of Theorick before his fall in battle were pieces of armour crafted out of pure ice, all of which have melted save for these shimmering boots. The coldest gales and most suffocating heat nurture and repair the wearer instead of being stifling or deadly.

Crusade Sabatons.name: Crusade Sabatons
Crusade Sabatons.addedLore: One of the very few physically-powerful artifacts of the Villagers, these boots were used in the initial crusades against the Green-skins, to overpower the Orcs via raw physical might. Though effective, they have not seen use in a long time.

Dawnbreak.name: Dawnbreak
Dawnbreak.addedLore: Many prophecies foretell of new eras. Most are fabricated or proven false in time. One passed through the Dogun caverns, however, tells of a dawn soon to break, in which the earth shall run red and return to flame. Fanatical sects whisper the coming of a new demonic god.

Galleon.name: Galleon
Galleon.addedLore: Forged with the raw powers of both the earth and the sea, these boots were initially an attempt at creating a method of foot-travel over the seas. Despite the spectacular failure of that application, they remain a formidable and reliable set of armor.

Moontower.name: Moontower
Moontower.addedLore: For the belief of the cosmos’ defilement, the moon was noted to remain unchanged. Those with this belief live only for the light of the moon, desperately seeking to maintain it through means that would only darken the soul of the most devout. Such from them comes the word lunacy.

Resurgence.name: Resurgence
Resurgence.addedLore: An antique passed from the Caritat wreckage into the hands of the outcast elves of Efilim. So to honor the memory of the selfless family as inspired their self-imposed exile, their strongest healing spells were imbued into it, and sent to those who needed them most.

Revenant.name: Revenant
Revenant.addedLore: Those whose souls are lost to the Canyon of the Lost eternally seek form. They inhabit those who wear these boots, unknowingly dragging the soul of the wearer into their ranks if worn for too long, leaving a wandering husk.

Slayer.name: Slayer
Slayer.addedLore: Many artifacts are found to incite rage in the wearer, and wizards old and new alike conjecture as to the purpose of them. Very few increase the latent abilities of the wearers to ensure havoc, and none to such a degree as these boots.

Stardew.name: Stardew
Stardew.addedLore: Wybels have a strange attraction to cosmic magic, and many an owner will find them staring through the window at night. One, however, claims to have seen her Wybel making something out of white stardust. The abode was robbed shortly after, and the supposed item gone missing without confirmation of its existence.

Warchief.name: Warchief
Warchief.addedLore: Sheer strength exudes from these Orcish relics, simple sandals ill-fitting to humans or Villagers. Enchanted with power and rage rather than magic, the strength that is provided when they are worn is unparalleled.

Meanderthal.name: Meanderthal
Meanderthal.addedLore: These boots were retrieved from a frozen man, uncovered on an expedition to Mt. Wynn. It is believed that the man had been wandering the world before his death.

Memento.name: Memento
Memento.addedLore: All those who wear these enchanted boots deposit a single fond memory into them. They are forgotten forever, but wearing them recalls every memory within vividly.

Abysso Galoshes.name: Abysso Galoshes
Abysso Galoshes.addedLore: Rumored to be crafted from a Dernic stone, these sinister boots radiate extremely powerful dark energy. They have absorbed the power of the raging seas in their time locked in Sarnfic.

Snowtread Boots.name: Snowtread Boots
Snowtread Boots.addedLore: According to the tag on the heels, these boots leave a trail of snow no matter  where one walks with them.

Sodeta Boots.name: Sodeta Boots
Sodeta Boots.addedLore: These boots were standard issue to members of the prestigious, and now disbanded, Sodeta Guild, and given as a gift to the owners of Delnar Mansion one day.

Nether's Scar.name: Nether's Scar
Nether's Scar.addedLore: Forged directly from the bloody red stone mined from the Nether, they were locked away for fear of inciting insanity in those who wore them.

Omnitread Boots.name: Omnitread Boots
Omnitread Boots.addedLore: Plated with enchanted metals, these magic-warding boots allow faster travel over nearly any solid surface.

Passus Lux.name: Passus Lux
Passus Lux.addedLore: A brilliant relic supposedly originating from the Realm of Light, the creators of these strangely shaped boots are completely unknown.

Enhanced Coalwalkers.name: Enhanced Coalwalkers
Enhanced Coalwalkers.addedLore: Even ignoring the numerous scorches all over, these boots hardly look any better.

Scorpio.name: Scorpio
Scorpio.addedLore: The carapace of the common Maexi pet fire scarabs, while alone, only cause minor burns to the touch. However, when woven together, they produce a variety of cumulative effects.

Seven-League Boots.name: Seven-League Boots
Seven-League Boots.addedLore: Bending the fabric of reality to allow the wearer to take massive strides, these boots are rumored to contain rogue djinni to power them.

Stalagmites.name: Stalagmites
Stalagmites.addedLore: Although these boots are crafted from corrupted stone, they do not exhibit any corruptive effects on their wearers. Speculation abounds as to the reason.

Steamjet Walkers.name: Steamjet Walkers
Steamjet Walkers.addedLore: A rogue inventor stole the plans for a steam jet booster from Corkus and reverse engineered them onto a set of boots. While effective, they are dangerous, prone to catastrophic failure.

Ventus Tail.name: Ventus Tail
Ventus Tail.addedLore: Fashioned from the cut tails of the now extinct Venti, these nearly immaterial boots are light as air and crackle with lightning.

Virgo.name: Virgo
Virgo.addedLore: These common leather boots were once owned by a barbarian with no magical prowess. Instead of enchanting it, he coated the soles in corrupted shards to punish those who opposed him.

Summa.name: Summa
Summa.addedLore: An auxiliary power core of the powerful TERA-4M Mining robot line. It controls the robots by giving the bearer a compulsion to break new grounds and progress further without heed.

Cold Wave.name: Cold Wave
Cold Wave.addedLore: Feeling the fresh chill of the cold air is all you need to know you're really alive.

Concentration.name: Concentration
Concentration.addedLore: The forger of this ring had to endure 30 long days of smelting various metals only found in the ocean. A single mistake would ruin the creation. The mystic metals are said to seep into the wearers skin to gently replenish their resolve.

Black Catalyst.name: Black Catalyst
Black Catalyst.addedLore: Even simply looking at these odd rings gives way to a compulsion to wear two of them, despite all better judgement.

Field.name: Field
Field.addedLore: "After the Nivla forest fire, I'm glad the corrupteds haven't thought to try and burn the Detlas Suburbs." -Sergeant Klafson, Detlas Legion

Rycar's Elation.name: Rycar's Elation
Rycar's Elation.addedLore: Created from the lip of a wine bottle and dropped in the mystic waters of Lake Gylia, this glass ring seems to follow Rycar's drunken escapades wherever she wanders.

Spider Ring.name: Spider Ring
Spider Ring.addedLore: "Crawly things. They crawl on the mushrooms. Mushrooms shouldn't be crawly!" -Yahya, Mushroom Man

Downfall.name: Downfall
Downfall.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] A fallen link from a chainmail hauberk of an older time, this ring fell from a giant taller than a mountain. As it sped through the air and  gained momentum, it traveled so fast that it was battered to a tenth of its size.

Intensity.name: Intensity
Intensity.addedLore: The runes carved into this simple gold ring translate into various words meaning power. It amplifies elemental energies in inexplicable ways.

Kaze.name: Kaze
Kaze.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Gentle spirits of the wind attract themselves to the brilliant jewels slotted into this ring, bringing peace to its wearers and those around them.

Bronze Basic Ring.name: Bronze Basic Ring
Bronze Basic Ring.addedLore: This ring is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

Diamond Fiber Ring.name: Diamond Fiber Ring
Diamond Fiber Ring.addedLore: This masterpiece of a ring utilizes powerful electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Wearing it, you can feel a deep connection to the ground below.

Diamond Fusion Ring.name: Diamond Fusion Ring
Diamond Fusion Ring.addedLore: This mighty ring is the crown jewel amongst elemental rings. Wearing it, your knowledge is no longer limited to a few elements.

Diamond Hydro Ring.name: Diamond Hydro Ring
Diamond Hydro Ring.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this ring on your finger, you could catch a gnat without looking.

Diamond Solar Ring.name: Diamond Solar Ring
Diamond Solar Ring.addedLore: The device forged into this flawless ring draws all heat from its surrounding. Though it almost burns, you can feel your abilites enhance.

Diamond Static Ring.name: Diamond Static Ring
Diamond Static Ring.addedLore: The heavy electrical impulses coming from this ring would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is pure power. A true masterpiece of engineering.

Diamond Steam Ring.name: Diamond Steam Ring
Diamond Steam Ring.addedLore: Users of this perfect model of Legendary Island's steam-powered ring have reported feeling weightless in combat. The jewel of the ring is a perfectly clear diamond.

Gold Fiber Ring.name: Gold Fiber Ring
Gold Fiber Ring.addedLore: This improved ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can sense a rhythm with each step...

Gold Fusion Ring.name: Gold Fusion Ring
Gold Fusion Ring.addedLore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a powerful elemental force in you. Though stronger than the previous model, its true potential stays sealed.

Gold Hydro Ring.name: Gold Hydro Ring
Gold Hydro Ring.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant insisted. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

Gold Static Ring.name: Gold Static Ring
Gold Static Ring.addedLore: The strong shock coming from this advanced version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

Gold Solar Ring.name: Gold Solar Ring
Gold Solar Ring.addedLore: The device forged into this advanced ring seems to absorb heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your hand...

Gold Steam Ring.name: Gold Steam Ring
Gold Steam Ring.addedLore: While this model of the Steam Ring is far superior to its predecessor, there still lies the capacity for one more upgrade. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

Silver Fiber Ring.name: Silver Fiber Ring
Silver Fiber Ring.addedLore: This crude looking ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

Silver Fusion Ring.name: Silver Fusion Ring
Silver Fusion Ring.addedLore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a strong elemental affinity in you. With some improvements to its core, it could become even better...

Silver Hydro Ring.name: Silver Hydro Ring
Silver Hydro Ring.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

Silver Solar Ring.name: Silver Solar Ring
Silver Solar Ring.addedLore: The device forged into this simple ring seems to absorb heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

Silver Steam Ring.name: Silver Steam Ring
Silver Steam Ring.addedLore: This prototype model of the Steam Ring increases the user's agility in combat. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

Silver Static Ring.name: Silver Static Ring
Silver Static Ring.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, mechanical ring without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

Lodestone.name: Lodestone
Lodestone.addedLore: The magical oddity known as lodestone has been studied for years as an active counterpart to quartz's passive magical properties. Research continues, but it is valuable when creating magical items.

Martyr.name: Martyr
Martyr.addedLore: A recently married man went off to war wearing this wedding ring. Though he perished in battle, his courage and determination empowers all who wear it.

Marvel.name: Marvel
Marvel.addedLore: The stellar quality of the coral jewels set into the ring comes from a magical purification process, involving a decade-long soak in mystical Gylia water.

Old Keeper's Ring.name: Old Keeper's Ring
Old Keeper's Ring.addedLore: Found on the corpse of the oldest shopkeeper of the Gavel province, the engraved text reads 'GREED'.

Precious.name: Precious
Precious.addedLore: A strange magic attracts you to this ring. Maybe you shouldn't tell anyone about its existence?

Prism.name: Prism
Prism.addedLore: The jewel on this ring is found very rarely deep beneath the Light Forest. It has the power to manipulate light itself.

Rarity.name: Rarity
Rarity.addedLore: Being one of the absolute rarest treasures in the world, it seems to have a mind of its own, only showing itself when a stroke of luck is had.

Chipped Glitz.name: Chipped Glitz
Chipped Glitz.addedLore: There are little chips and cracks all over this... was someone trying to break it down for gold?

Broken Sandust.name: Broken Sandust
Broken Sandust.addedLore: The silver looks rather tarnished...does he expect you to believe that "gem" isn't just a cheap glass bauble?

Cracked Stonehall.name: Cracked Stonehall
Cracked Stonehall.addedLore: It looks like someone tried and failed to improve it. The re-smithing job was obviously rushed...

Unspeakable.name: Unspeakable
Unspeakable.addedLore: The wielders of this cursed glassen bauble are rendered mute. The effect is reversed after the item is removed, but the longer it is worn, the longer the curse remains.

Binding Brace.name: Binding Brace
Binding Brace.addedLore: An oppressively dark aura emanates from this shackle, dampening both the will and magic potency of those that wear it.

Buster Bracer.name: Buster Bracer
Buster Bracer.addedLore: A mighty, earth-shatteringly powerful weapon was destroyed for fear of its raw power, and the pieces buried. They were unearthed decades later, and were reforged into various items including this sturdy bracer.

Call to Concord.name: Call to Concord
Call to Concord.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Reverberating with the bravery and residual strength of fallen Wynn soldiers, every casualty only serves to harden the resolve it instills in the wearer.

Vitre.name: Vitre
Vitre.addedLore: "They say the eyes are the windows to the soul. That's ridiculous, ocular fluids are primarily opaque." -Ragon, Elemental Researcher

Remikas' Authority.name: Remikas' Authority
Remikas' Authority.addedLore: This plain-looking silver bracer is one of the last surviving heirlooms of the first Gavellian king, to be passed down to his heirs. The shimmering metal is said to contain Remikas' soul within it.

Ra.name: Ra
Ra.addedLore: Undecipherable symbols are carved into this long arm band, though the fiery glow and bright jewel has led archaeologists to believe it is somehow related to the sun.

Double Vision.name: Double Vision
Double Vision.quest: Realm of Light V - The Realm of Light

Follow The Wind.name: Follow The Wind
Follow The Wind.addedLore: A lost relic from the Wind Fortress, a mythical stronghold of the Sky Islands that fell into the Void long ago. A small mechanism within the bracelet points towards its place of origin.

Prowess.name: Prowess
Prowess.addedLore: The runes carved into this simple gold cuff translate into various words meaning mastery. It amplifies the ability of the wearer in mysterious ways.

Jiandan Handwraps.name: Jiandan Handwraps
Jiandan Handwraps.addedLore: The cloth wraps produced by the canyon Dojo are just that, merely soft cloth. It is left to the users to apply them skillfully in battle, in whatever way they see fit.

Knucklebones.name: Knucklebones
Knucklebones.addedLore: An old Nemract saying is engraved along the metal. "A single toss of the knucklebones can make or break a gambling man."

Bronze Basic Bracelet.name: Bronze Basic Bracelet
Bronze Basic Bracelet.addedLore: This bracelet is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

Diamond Fiber Bracelet.name: Diamond Fiber Bracelet
Diamond Fiber Bracelet.addedLore: Desired by many of the countless challengers, this bracelet allows you to sense movements over thousands of meters away. It is decorated with rough yet beautiful jewels.

Diamond Fusion Bracelet.name: Diamond Fusion Bracelet
Diamond Fusion Bracelet.addedLore: This bracelet opens up its wearers spirit, filling it with pure elemental knowledge. The ornaments decorating it are without peer.

Diamond Hydro Bracelet.name: Diamond Hydro Bracelet
Diamond Hydro Bracelet.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this bracelet on your arm you could ride a wave with your bare feet.

Diamond Solar Bracelet.name: Diamond Solar Bracelet
Diamond Solar Bracelet.addedLore: The device forged into this perfected bracelet drains all heat from its surroundings. Though it almost burns, you can feel your power growing

Diamond Static Bracelet.name: Diamond Static Bracelet
Diamond Static Bracelet.addedLore: The heavy shocks coming from this perfected bracelet would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is the enhancement of power.

Diamond Steam Bracelet.name: Diamond Steam Bracelet
Diamond Steam Bracelet.addedLore: This steam-powered bracelet is sought by many challengers of the Legendary Challenge. They say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

Gold Fiber Bracelet.name: Gold Fiber Bracelet
Gold Fiber Bracelet.addedLore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can feel a rhythm with each step...

Gold Fusion Bracelet.name: Gold Fusion Bracelet
Gold Fusion Bracelet.addedLore: This bracelet, decorated with complex ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. Though powerful, there's still a lot to improve.

Gold Hydro Bracelet.name: Gold Hydro Bracelet
Gold Hydro Bracelet.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

Gold Solar Bracelet.name: Gold Solar Bracelet
Gold Solar Bracelet.addedLore: The device forged into this improved bracelet seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your arm...

Gold Static Bracelet.name: Gold Static Bracelet
Gold Static Bracelet.addedLore: The painful shock coming from this improved version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

Gold Steam Bracelet.name: Gold Steam Bracelet
Gold Steam Bracelet.addedLore: This impressive bracelet is in high demand. Those who have obtained it say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

Silver Fusion Bracelet.name: Silver Fusion Bracelet
Silver Fusion Bracelet.addedLore: This bracelet, decorated with simple ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

Silver Solar Bracelet.name: Silver Solar Bracelet
Silver Solar Bracelet.addedLore: The device forged into this simple bracelet seems to gather heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

Silver Hydro Bracelet.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.
