Silver Fiber Bracelet.addedLore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

Silver Static Bracelet.name: Silver Static Bracelet
Silver Static Bracelet.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the simple, mechanical bracelet without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

Silver Steam Bracelet.name: Silver Steam Bracelet
Silver Steam Bracelet.addedLore: Users who have worn this early model of the Steam Bracelet have reported that they have felt "one with the wind" while wearing it.

Momentum.name: Momentum
Momentum.addedLore: This golden cuff has an odd time dilation effect surrounding it, slowing all movements significantly, but multiplying the force of impact to a significant degree.

Anya's Penumbra.name: Anya's Penumbra
Anya's Penumbra.addedLore: "The lightest light will never defeat the darkest dark. Only those who understand both can survive."

Used Wolf Paw.name: Used Wolf Paw
Used Wolf Paw.addedLore: It looks more like a dog paw to you, but you don't feel like risking your life arguing with the merchant.

Durum's Serenity.name: Durum's Serenity
Durum's Serenity.addedLore: Carried by the Durum Protector, this small necklace holds but an ounce of the vibrance and life of the Durum Isles.

Adder Stone.name: Adder Stone
Adder Stone.addedLore: Aldorei charms are often shared and tinkered with by gifted Elves within the commune. Though simple, the stones blessed by elven magic provide soothing energy to the wearer.

Ensa's Faith.name: Ensa's Faith
Ensa's Faith.addedLore: The scholar-priest Ensa created this pendant as a personal prayer while his home was under siege. It is rumored to hold the key to enlightenment, but it is unknown as to how.

Witherhead's Talisman.name: Witherhead's Talisman
Witherhead's Talisman.addedLore: "My dear boy should never have to go through the horrors of losing a mother like that." -Momo, adoptive mother of Bob

Contrast.name: Contrast
Contrast.addedLore: The runes carved onto the gold beads strung along this simple necklace translate into various words meaning variance. It provides many abilities though unexplainable means.

Hexed Amulet.name: Hexed Amulet
Hexed Amulet.addedLore: Although the warlock's curse placed upon this simple, Olux-crafted charm will reduce the abilities of the wearer significantly, its original luck-bolstering properties still are in place.

Bronze Basic Necklace.name: Bronze Basic Necklace
Bronze Basic Necklace.addedLore: This necklace is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

Diamond Fiber Necklace.name: Diamond Fiber Necklace
Diamond Fiber Necklace.addedLore: This ultimate version of a necklace was given to less than a handful of adventurers. Once on your neck, you can communicate with the ground below as if you grew roots.

Diamond Fusion Necklace.name: Diamond Fusion Necklace
Diamond Fusion Necklace.addedLore: Unlike any other invention this necklace enhances your power and understanding of the elements tenfold. The colorful jewels used are almost dizzying you.

Diamond Hydro Necklace.name: Diamond Hydro Necklace
Diamond Hydro Necklace.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said and every word was true. With this necklace equipped, you could hear the ocean whisper.

Diamond Solar Necklace.name: Diamond Solar Necklace
Diamond Solar Necklace.addedLore: The masterpiece of a necklace gathers all heat from its surrounding. It is fed to its wearer to maximize the strength of attacks.

Diamond Static Necklace.name: Diamond Static Necklace
Diamond Static Necklace.addedLore: The lethal amount of electricity emmited from this often desired necklace fails to kill you, as its pure energy runs through your veins.

Gold Fiber Necklace.name: Gold Fiber Necklace
Gold Fiber Necklace.addedLore: This improved version of a bracelet utilizes rare electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You notice a rhythm with each step...

Diamond Steam Necklace.name: Diamond Steam Necklace
Diamond Steam Necklace.addedLore: This necklace is the pinnacle of steam-powered technology. Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from the necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all.

Gold Fusion Necklace.name: Gold Fusion Necklace
Gold Fusion Necklace.addedLore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses advanced nano-technology to boost its users elemental abilities. Though powerful, there are still a few flaws to be fixed.

Gold Hydro Necklace.name: Gold Hydro Necklace
Gold Hydro Necklace.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

Gold Solar Necklace.name: Gold Solar Necklace
Gold Solar Necklace.addedLore: The device forged into this advanced necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your neck...

Gold Static Necklace.name: Gold Static Necklace
Gold Static Necklace.addedLore: The strong shock coming from this improved version of the necklace is a small price for its strength, but it has yet to reach its peak.

Gold Steam Necklace.name: Gold Steam Necklace
Gold Steam Necklace.addedLore: The jewel hanging from this necklace is said to be weightless. While still very powerful, its full potential has yet to be achieved.

Legendary Medallion.name: Legendary Medallion
Legendary Medallion.addedLore: This medallion marks its wearer as a true champion. It is awarded to those who have put an unnecessary amount of time into attempting the Legendary Challenge.

Silver Fiber Necklace.name: Silver Fiber Necklace
Silver Fiber Necklace.addedLore: This crude looking necklace utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains quiet.

Silver Fusion Necklace.name: Silver Fusion Necklace
Silver Fusion Necklace.addedLore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

Silver Solar Necklace.name: Silver Solar Necklace
Silver Solar Necklace.addedLore: The device forged into this basic necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warm sting when holding it.

Silver Static Necklace.name: Silver Static Necklace
Silver Static Necklace.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, tech-enhanced necklace without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

Silver Steam Necklace.name: Silver Steam Necklace
Silver Steam Necklace.addedLore: Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from this necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all. However, the necklace's mechanisms seem incomplete.

Silver Hydro Necklace.name: Silver Hydro Necklace
Silver Hydro Necklace.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

Master.name: Master
Master.addedLore: Although not truly magical by any means, the sheer craftsmanship of this ornate broach makes its wearers feel skillful.

Abyssal Amulet.name: Abyssal Amulet
Abyssal Amulet.addedLore: Used by the Order of the Abyss to aid their summoning rituals, it contains a strange, fiery energy. It has ties with a terrible demon...

Altum Spatium.name: Altum Spatium
Altum Spatium.addedLore: Even looking at this pendant strains your eyes. Should it even exist?

Royal Blazing Amulet.name: Royal Blazing Amulet
Royal Blazing Amulet.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It glows with a comforting warmth.

Royal Stormy Amulet.name: Royal Stormy Amulet
Royal Stormy Amulet.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It pulsates with a calming aura.

Royal Dusty Amulet.name: Royal Dusty Amulet
Royal Dusty Amulet.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It shines with a powerful strength.

Royal Cyclone Amulet.name: Royal Cyclone Amulet
Royal Cyclone Amulet.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It whistles with an invigorating tune.

Royal Shocking Amulet.name: Royal Shocking Amulet
Royal Shocking Amulet.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It crackles with a chaotic energy.

Wynnterfest 2016 Souvenir.name: Wynnterfest 2016 Souvenir
Wynnterfest 2016 Souvenir.addedLore: Thank you for participating in Wynnterfest 2016!

Wynnter Fair 2016 Souvenir.name: Wynnter Fair 2016 Souvenir
Wynnter Fair 2016 Souvenir.addedLore: Thank you for participating in the 2016 Wynnter Fair!

Necklace of a Thousand Storms.name: Necklace of a Thousand Storms
Necklace of a Thousand Storms.addedLore: Sealed away by the Avos of the old days to prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, this necklace was enchanted to strengthen its wearers spiritual link to nature itself.

Wynnter Fair 2017 Souvenir.name: Wynnter Fair 2017 Souvenir
Wynnter Fair 2017 Souvenir.addedLore: Thank you for participating in the 2017 Wynnter Fair!

Planet Healer.name: Planet Healer
Planet Healer.addedLore: The jewels in this necklace naturally draw darkness and corruption into its wearer, purifying the land around them at the cost of their own life.

Shatterglass.name: Shatterglass
Shatterglass.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] This small, rough-crafted pendant is the only known magic artifact of the Orcs. It incites destructive tendencies within the wearer.

Stellar.name: Stellar
Stellar.addedLore: Elementally attuned gemstones are melded together to form the singular marvel found on this pendant. Despite the violent smithing process, the jewel is utterly flawless.

Tenuto.name: Tenuto
Tenuto.addedLore: This strange pendant has been known to dilate time around the wearer, slowing their movements while greatly augmenting their power.

Helm Splitter.name: Helm Splitter
Helm Splitter.addedLore: One of Skien's many deadly weapons. This warhammer, despite the massive weight of the hammerhead, was able to be swung by Skien fast enough to be a blur.

Kahontsi Ohstyen.name: Kahontsi Ohstyen
Kahontsi Ohstyen.addedLore: Wielded by the chief of the Tromsian jungle's zombie tribes, the augmentable crystals within it focus natural elemental energies to intense levels.

Plague Staff.name: Plague Staff
Plague Staff.addedLore: Carried by the Olux Plague Doctor, this simple-looking stick subtly oozes with an unidentifiable substance that is invigorating to the holder, and lethally venomous to anything else.

Blade of Shade.name: Blade of Shade
Blade of Shade.addedLore: The fabled weapon of the titular dark Assassin, the blade's small stature hides its true powers. Shadows undulate about the hilt.

Panic Zealot.name: Panic Zealot
Panic Zealot.addedLore: They must know what you went through. They must suffer the same as you did.

Deadeye.name: Deadeye
Deadeye.addedLore: The weapon of the fearsome lone bandit, Rymek Luke, it is unique in that it is designed to fire small metal rounds instead of more traditional projectiles.

Haros' Oar.name: Haros' Oar
Haros' Oar.addedLore: The weathered oar of Haros, the outcast ferryman of Charon's Forsaken Legion. Magical implements have been jury-rigged onto the silver pole, glowing dull out of his bony grasp.

Stave of the Legends.name: Stave of the Legends
Stave of the Legends.addedLore: Crafted exclusively by the Temple of the Legends' mages, this stave is honorary to Mages who best the Temple's Grand Magus.

Lower.name: Lower
Lower.addedLore: The name has got to be misspelled... It doesn't even make any sense!

Braker.name: Braker
Braker.addedLore: Seems like the name is misspelled a little bit.

Slider.name: Slider
Slider.addedLore: The spelling seems to have been botched.

Bonder.name: Bonder
Bonder.addedLore: It looks like they spelled the name wrong...

Stinger.name: Stinger
Stinger.addedLore: If it weren't for that stray mark, this would be spelled correctly...

Afterimage.name: Afterimage
Afterimage.addedLore: This wand is capable of attacks so fast that it appears to flicker in and out of existence. Anyone able to access its full potential will be seen as only a blur to their enemies.

Alazarin.name: Alazarin
Alazarin.addedLore: This bloody palette knife was used to kill only two people before it was abandoned - a killer who broke into a great artist's home, and the artist who struck the blow.

Alka Cometflinger.name: Alka Cometflinger
Alka Cometflinger.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and raw potential fuse to create an imposing presence, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for complete obliteration.

Almuj's Daggers.name: Almuj's Daggers
Almuj's Daggers.addedLore: The reigning king of thieves in Almuj’s underworld would brandish this golden dagger to his enemies so fast, you wouldn’t even realise your wallet was now missing.

Ancient Wand.name: Ancient Wand
Ancient Wand.addedLore: It is thought that this primitive wand was used by early man to create the first spells. It is made from a wood that no longer exists.

Arma Gauntlet.name: Arma Gauntlet
Arma Gauntlet.addedLore: Stories say that should anyone wield both of these fearsome gauntlets in battle, they will become unkillable in a fight. The second gauntlet, however, has never been found.

Bedruthan.name: Bedruthan
Bedruthan.addedLore: Stone shorn from mountains by the roiling sea gathered on the shores of Llevigar one day, washed onto the sand in the shape of a massive spear. It was taken as an omen, and the stones were forged into a true weapon.

Bismuthinite.name: Bismuthinite
Bismuthinite.addedLore: An extremely rare metallic ore only found within the island region of Corkus, it is normally used in decorative dyes. However, a mishap one day caused the discovery of strange and cumulative effects when exposed to traditional magicks.

Black.name: Black
Black.addedLore: Hewn from the great obsidian spires surrounding the massive Nether gate, this fiercely-hooked dagger absorbs light and magic energy alike to create a desolate void wherever it is wielded.

Blade of Purity.name: Blade of Purity
Blade of Purity.addedLore: The creator of this polished white blade insists that its true power will never be unlocked, for only those who are not influenced by the elements of the world know truly how to utilize it.

Blossom.name: Blossom
Blossom.addedLore: A mystical sapling native to the shores of Mage Island has been fashioned into this simple staff. Even uprooted, you notice its continuous growth.

Blossom Haze.name: Blossom Haze
Blossom Haze.addedLore: And as the spring bursts, the blossom petals flutter in the wind amongst the ashes of your enemies.

Bough of Fir.name: Bough of Fir
Bough of Fir.addedLore: Crafted from Mandragora roots and adorned with decorative wreaths of Elven pines, these wands are utilized in Efilim's solstice festivals to celebrate each passing year of Villager and Elven comradery.

Brass Brand.name: Brass Brand
Brass Brand.addedLore: Built by Cerid to accrue raw static charge from the surroundings and direct it at opponents, the blade's chief failing is that the wielder is not rendered immune to their own discharge as intended.

Wybel Paw.name: Wybel Paw
Wybel Paw.addedLore: Even reduced to just the bones, you can't help but feel bad for the poor thing this paw came from.

Cascade.name: Cascade
Cascade.addedLore: A great magical cataclysm at Mage Island brought on by a strange, seemingly disconnected series of events resulted in this wand absorbing nearly uncontrollably high levels of magic.

Chaleur.name: Chaleur
Chaleur.addedLore: This blackiron blade was left to sear in the desert for months on end by a fanatical berserker. It burned him alive as he cut down those who opposed him.

Chakram.name: Chakram
Chakram.addedLore: Despite appearing as a basic blade when held, strange spiritual magic changes its form into a sharp, ring-like cutting edge when used to attack. Only one person was known to master the weapon's abilities.

Clairvoyance.name: Clairvoyance
Clairvoyance.addedLore: The powerful psychic energies surrounding this bow are rumored to increase accuracy, though this has not been refuted by any reliable source.

Clash Hook.name: Clash Hook
Clash Hook.addedLore: The wear on this humble war pick's blade has only made it more effective in combat, allowing its users to make unexpected parries of opponents' attacks by hooking and hitting through the weapon.

Cluster.name: Cluster
Cluster.addedLore: Perhaps one is weak. To be ignored. Perhaps two are not much better. But what of five? Ten? Twenty?...

Crackshot.name: Crackshot
Crackshot.addedLore: This heavy crossbow forces a strange compulsion in its users when wielded. They will often refuse to even shoot unless entirely certain of a hit.

Witherhead's Bow.name: Witherhead's Bow
Witherhead's Bow.addedLore: Wielded by the master of the Decrepit Sewers Dungeon, the arrows of this bow causes the target's body to slowly wither away.

Sprout.name: Sprout
Sprout.addedLore: "The plants loathe to take hold upon the red stone. And so, we must hunt instead."  -Caras, Owl Tribesman

Chaser.name: Chaser
Chaser.addedLore: "My husband's such a scaredy-cat. What good is tomb raiding if you're not in the tomb?"  -Dr. Junes, Almuj Archaeologist

Clunderthap.name: Clunderthap
Clunderthap.addedLore: "It never rains here, but we hear the thunder echoing in the distance."  -Lanu, Almuj Archaeomancer

Jaw Breaker.name: Jaw Breaker
Jaw Breaker.addedLore: "Bandit attacks losing you sleep? Free fighting classes here! Only 10  emeralds- they won't know what hit 'em!" -Almuj Self-Defense Class Advertisement

Hashr Claw.name: Hashr Claw
Hashr Claw.addedLore: "Betrayal stings sharper than a scorpion's tail, and festers worse than the poison inside."   -Attributed to Hashr

Karma.name: Karma
Karma.addedLore: "When payback is the rule of the land, it feels safest to do nothing."  -Ormrod, Self-exiled Almuj Resident

Miasma.name: Miasma
Miasma.addedLore: "I have to wonder just how healthy slime found in the depths of a desert  cavern can be to drink." -Eluzterp, Almuj resident

Sol.name: Sol
Sol.addedLore: "The sun and related symbols appear quite often in these ancient glyphs.  Interesting, but unsurprising, no?" -Svin, Legend Keeper

Corpse.name: Corpse
Corpse.addedLore: "Catch a fresh-raised corrupted, it's like catching a soldier without his morning coffee. Stumbly and unfocused." -Enzan, Retired Ragni Soldier

Tremolo.name: Tremolo
Tremolo.addedLore: "It feels like all these "ancient" civilizations have better tech than we do nowadays."  -Knox, Corkus Immigrant and Sandstorm Vandals bandit

Defibrillator.name: Defibrillator
Defibrillator.addedLore: "The first time I saw one of those zombies I nearly had a heart attack! The blighters are terrifying." -Rynend, Maltic Citizen

Stale.name: Stale
Stale.addedLore: "There's never new water flowing into those sewers. It all cycles back into itself...not natural." -Jenprest, Ragni Legion 2nd Division

Serpent's Kiss.name: Serpent's Kiss
Serpent's Kiss.addedLore: "I bet those sewer-dwellers have horrible morning breath." -Folzoy, Maltic Escort

Macabre.name: Macabre
Macabre.addedLore: "Only the most wicked in Gavel could dream of a circumstance as what plagues this Wynn province." -King of Ragni

Sketiq.name: Sketiq
Sketiq.addedLore: "As much as they're terrifying, at least those lousy skeletons give us lots of bonemeal for the crops!" -Bylvis, Katoa Ranch Farmer

Hourglass.name: Hourglass
Hourglass.addedLore: "I saw that spider queen once. It felt like it was only a matter of time before she found my home, so I moved here." -Babhla, Nivla Bowl Merchant

Skull Breaker.name: Skull Breaker
Skull Breaker.addedLore: "Even a corrupted would get crushed by one of these!" -Roche 'Stone-thrower' Diamant, Ragni Citizen

Fangs.name: Fangs
Fangs.addedLore: "Not every spider is venomous, but do you really want to get bitten by them all to figure out which are?" -Alvin, Nivla Forest Resident

Sting.name: Sting
Sting.addedLore: "I swear on my life those spiders were covered in spikes! Go out there, see if I'm wrong!" -Suri, Elemental Researcher

Maul.name: Maul
Maul.addedLore: "If you squish a spider egg, sometimes little spiders pop out. So, squish the whole area instead!" -Captain Fenor, Detlas Legion

Iklaj.name: Iklaj
Iklaj.addedLore: "I am not making this up! That spider teleported ONTO MY FACE!" -Stiba, Elemental Researcher

Abolition.name: Abolition
Abolition.addedLore: "Those bloody zombies don't kip down at night, what makes you think a curfew might bally-well help?" -General Graken, Nemract Militia

Damnation.name: Damnation
Damnation.addedLore: "I got a name, known far and wide! Run along, you bandit scum, before you have to learn it the hard way!" -Sayleros' Brother, killed by bandits

Death's Reach.name: Death's Reach
Death's Reach.addedLore: "We'll ensure that under our watch, all your families will be reunited!" -Haros, of the Banished Legion

Web Spitter.name: Web Spitter
Web Spitter.addedLore: "And you thought walking into a cobweb was bad." -Ope, Ragni Botanist

Cathedral.name: Cathedral
Cathedral.addedLore: "The gravestone for the brother of that man, Sayleros? For whatever reason, it didn't have a proper name on it." -Sacre, Saint's Row Priest

Hymn of the Dead.name: Hymn of the Dead
Hymn of the Dead.addedLore: "The dead can still hear. I figure a lullaby might help convince them to sleep a bit longer." -Merloni, Saint's Row Priest

Putrid.name: Putrid
Putrid.addedLore: "Leave us down here to die, why don't you all. Just turn us into another statistic and be done, huh?" -Ragamal, Nemract Sewer Dweller

Thriller.name: Thriller
Thriller.addedLore: "And no one's going to save us from the beasts about to strike. We've seen horrors stare us in the eyes, and we're fighting for our lives." -Poe, Nemract Sewer Dweller

Sanies.name: Sanies
Sanies.addedLore: "Can anyone else understand that General Graken? Because I can't." -Commander Takan, Nemract Militia

Styx's Grab.name: Styx's Grab
Styx's Grab.addedLore: "Never wish to see a dead loved one again. In this day and age, they'll come back to see you." -Mylo, Nemract Conscript

Detlas' Legacy.name: Detlas' Legacy
Detlas' Legacy.addedLore: One of Detlas’ buildings was struck by lightning 60 years ago and burnt to the ground, apart from one wooden beam that began to glow. It was fashioned into an exclusive wand for resident mages.

Diablo.name: Diablo
Diablo.addedLore: One of the most unstable wands known to man, using the bark of the Flerisi trunk it reaps firey destruction upon its enemies.

Dislocater.name: Dislocater
Dislocater.addedLore: Often, the leader of brute gangs would use this dagger to threaten his followers into making sure they did not fail him.

Empire Builder.name: Empire Builder
Empire Builder.addedLore: This golden staff was recovered from deep within the tombs of Almuj. Nothing else was found in the room except the words 'Beware the user with unlimited imagination.'

Eruption.name: Eruption
Eruption.addedLore: No one expected the WynnExcavation volcanic site to produce any valuable materials, but this heavy, obsidian-blend bow silenced the critics.

Ethereal.name: Ethereal
Ethereal.addedLore: Supposedly based off of the wand of master mage Ethe, this wand is plated with magic-focusing jewels and heavy gold, yet somehow remains entirely weightless.

Faustian Contract.name: Faustian Contract
Faustian Contract.addedLore: Once a contract is formed, and before its details are discussed, a seal is placed on the human's body.

Fierce Thunder.name: Fierce Thunder
Fierce Thunder.addedLore: Every time this spear hits an enemy, a sharp electrical jolt hits the users hands that forces powerful lightning to release.

Fierte.name: Fierte
Fierte.addedLore: Only the most honourable warriors of Gavel's army are presented the trident shaped spear, forged from the rarest metal from the molten heights.

Fissure.name: Fissure
Fissure.addedLore: Dwarven folklore tells of this mighty maul, used by gods to break mountains, shape continents, and crack the earth to form caverns.

Flameshot Hilt.name: Flameshot Hilt
Flameshot Hilt.addedLore: Found abandoned in the ruins of the Doguns, these odd weapons are designed to shoot jets of sheer flame instead of hitting enemies traditionally. They are in terrible disrepair, and none know how to fix them.

Gert Super Special Magic Ultistick.name: Gert Super Special Magic Ultistick
Gert Super Special Magic Ultistick.addedLore: Well...it is a very pretty-looking stick, but aside from that it just appears to be a plain old stick.

Gale's Force.name: Gale's Force
Gale's Force.addedLore: Those who have used this near-weightless bow all seem to tell tales of how they see Gale's spirit fighting alongside them.

Glacial Crest.name: Glacial Crest
Glacial Crest.addedLore: Used for endurance training on the Icy Islands, this bow forces the wielder's body temperature to drop to near-hypothermic levels.

Glare.name: Glare
Glare.addedLore: The blazing sun has been revered by many druidic sects as a god in its own right, and the jewel in this brilliant wand glows with the brightness of their holy star.

Infused Hive Relik.name: Infused Hive Relik
Infused Hive Relik.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this relik has been infused with energy from all five known elements. The head gleams in a spectrum of colors.

Infused Hive Bow.name: Infused Hive Bow
Infused Hive Bow.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this bow has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its string radiates a spectrum of colors.

Infused Hive Dagger.name: Infused Hive Dagger
Infused Hive Dagger.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this dagger has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It leaves afterimages that pulsate in a spectrum of colors.

Infused Hive Spear.name: Infused Hive Spear
Infused Hive Spear.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this spear has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its tip shimmers in a spectrum of colors.

Infused Hive Wand.name: Infused Hive Wand
Infused Hive Wand.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this wand has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It subtly glows in a spectrum of colors.

Harwrol.name: Harwrol
Harwrol.addedLore: The runes carved onto the spear shift appearance so quickly as to be illegible, but those who wield it supposedly will learn their meaning.

Harsh Noise.name: Harsh Noise
Harsh Noise.addedLore: Corkian technology was not the first to create an item that is capable  of recording noise. Artifacts from Time Valley were found to record ambient  sounds and distort them into ear-splitting sonic bursts.

Heat Death.name: Heat Death
Heat Death.addedLore: Everything slowly loses heat, and will eventually stop moving. Are you prepared?

Hellstrand.name: Hellstrand
Hellstrand.addedLore: The Order of the Abyss crafted this bow in opposition to the House of Talor's holy relic. Holding it for too long will strain and warp the user's mind.

Heracul.name: Heracul
Heracul.addedLore: Reconstructed from mere wooden scraps of its former self, this extremely heavy crossbow still contains immense power. It was intended for use with a lost suit of armor, of which only one piece remains.

Hesperium.name: Hesperium
Hesperium.addedLore: Watch as they receive your gift of imminent disaster and endless fallout.

Ignition.name: Ignition
Ignition.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Forged with flaming scales shorn from Ozoth, the fabled Golden Ninja of the Canyon of the Lost hunted his prey relentlessly using this lightweight, yet harder than steel, polearm.

Impulse.name: Impulse
Impulse.addedLore: Prolonged exposure to the corruption may cause sudden bursts of madness in soldiers. To assure themselves of their sanity, some have even begun to play tricks on their brethren.

Infinity.name: Infinity
Infinity.addedLore: If you reach for ammunition from your quiver, as long as you have a single arrow, you will find you never run out.

Influence.name: Influence
Influence.addedLore: This knife does not belong in your hands... yet somehow it feels right at home.

Iron Knuckle.name: Iron Knuckle
Iron Knuckle.addedLore: These bulky-looking gauntlets are actually extremely lightweight, being created of a magical elf-blessed iron alloy blend.

Iron String.name: Iron String
Iron String.addedLore: Many said making a bow out of iron would be slow and wasteful, but the weight of the iron arrow can pierce even stone.

Ivory.name: Ivory
Ivory.addedLore: The holy blade of the House of Talor was crafted of pure unicorn horns, and consecrated by a hundred priests. Evil spirits are driven away by its mere presence.

Legendary Smasher.name: Legendary Smasher
Legendary Smasher.addedLore: Many have tried to duplicate the properties of this spear, but very few have succeeded in enchanting a spearhead with explosive magic that does not cause the spear itself to explode.

Locrian.name: Locrian
Locrian.addedLore: Skien's trust in others was shattered permanently by the wielder of this dagger, who fell to the corruption and attacked his legion during a great corrupted siege.

Lunar Spine.name: Lunar Spine
Lunar Spine.addedLore: From the Nether Gate, a shard of cosmic stone was ejected. Its purity was defiled, and the first man to wield it went mad, raving about the fall of the cosmos' beauty.

Apocalypse.name: Apocalypse
Apocalypse.addedLore: Forged from the tooth of the fallen one, this spear was bargained to a human for his soul, not knowing that the weapon itself would claim all life.

Alkatraz.name: Alkatraz
Alkatraz.addedLore: Soul-locking magic is one outlawed by Gavellian governments, only used by the most insidious and cruel of mages. One such enchantment looms dormant in this mundane-looking maul. Continued usage of the weapon threatens to release it upon the wielder, permanently binding them to the weapon.

Az.name: Az
Az.addedLore: Mysterious runes, held by inexplicable ancient guardians, were once moulded together for study purposes. The experiment went awry, as the runic words Nii, Az, and Ek were combined in a reaction that resulted in the collapse of a civilization.

Collapse.name: Collapse
Collapse.addedLore: Despite the light weight of the weapon, the spearhead has been made from incredibly dense cosmic stone. A strong enough impact can directly destroy matter. Due to this danger, it is sought after to be destroyed.

Archangel.name: Archangel
Archangel.addedLore: The unwieldy, yet imposing stature of this massive sickle strikes awe into those who view it. Those who have the will to wield it, however, seem to garner respect from all those around them, as though they had become a god.

Cataclysm.name: Cataclysm
Cataclysm.addedLore: Despite the existence of the Nether Portal, few believe that it is possible to open such rifts with sheer force alone. None believe that a tool with enough power to accomplish such a monumental feat could exist. And yet...

Divzer.name: Divzer
Divzer.addedLore: Unruly magics of void and darkness are tamed within this bow's string. While those energies are never to be released, arrows fired from it fire at such blinding speeds so as to phase out of existence when they hit their target.

Fatal.name: Fatal
Fatal.addedLore: A mage by the name of Lero claims to have harnessed the sheer power of lightning using a magical staff, however, the weapon is very unreliable in a pinch.

Freedom.name: Freedom
Freedom.addedLore: Freedom of soul, mind, and body are forced upon all those that this bow's arrows impact, and freedom of caring from the atrocities that such a dangerous weapon can inflict is given to all those that hold it.

Gaia.name: Gaia
Gaia.addedLore: The Dernel tribes revere various nature deities, each in their own unique fashions. One of the most notable was that of a lost tribe, who fashioned this blossoming stave as tribute to their deity of the earth itself.

Grandmother.name: Grandmother
Grandmother.addedLore: The very first crossbow in existence was claimed to be utterly indestructible, but it is only true to a fault. The item cannot be broken, but solely because all damage to it is instead reflected onto the user. As its age is uncountably ancient, wielders will find themselves rapidly aging and withering away with even a mere touch.

Ignis.name: Ignis
Ignis.addedLore: This bow, used by the dwarves to land the final blow in the slaughter of Garaheth is extremely powerful. Special, fire resistant gloves must be worn at all times to prevent burns to the user.

Guardian.name: Guardian
Guardian.addedLore: A vow of protection hangs over this spear, now inhabited by the spirit of a legendary heroine. Even simply a glimpse of the burning blade will instill a feeling of protection and security, and that feeling will hold true if one is brave enough to wield it.

Grimtrap.name: Grimtrap
Grimtrap.addedLore: Found at the site of the Caritat Mansion, this simple-looking glove is bathed in dark presence. It wracks those who wear it with pain, and instills the belief that the only way to end the pain is not to remove the item, but to inflict that same torment upon all others.

Inferno.name: Inferno
Inferno.addedLore: The Dogun God Garaheth was actually an immense fire demon occupying the bowels of Molten Heights. Although unwise, the Dwarves forged a demonic dagger using his tooth in celebration of his slaughter.

Hero.name: Hero
Hero.addedLore: Enigmatically, this weapon will only show itself to those who believe themselves to be worth nothing, or to be weak. While utilizing this weapon will greatly strengthen one's resolve, it will disappear when it is no longer needed, going to the next wielder.

Monster.name: Monster
Monster.addedLore: This wand merges with the user on touch, bringing about horrific changes to them. Elongated nails, sharp teeth and the ability to breathe fire are trademarks of the beast.

Idol.name: Idol
Idol.addedLore: Intricate carvings and images, almost like that of a totem pole, cover the shaft of this marvelous trident, dredged up from the Seavale Reef. Foreign magics heighten the senses of its user in battle, but also instills a longing for the ocean. Many have succumbed to this urge and drowned themselves.

Lament.name: Lament
Lament.addedLore: When the lost city of Sarnfic sunk beneath the depths, nothing but the bubbles of screams and this single wand surfaced. When used, you can still hear the towns lament.

Nullification.name: Nullification
Nullification.addedLore: The diminutive stature of this item belies its abilities. Absorbing and expelling magical energy in precise bursts, it protects the user from all manner of attacks while punishing those who dare strike.

Nirvana.name: Nirvana
Nirvana.addedLore: Spiritual enlightenment is a goal that many monks hope to one day grasp the barest glimpse of, often thought to be a goal that must be worked towards over a lifetime. Holding this polished, translucent blade will instantly induce that lofty state until it is let go.

Pure.name: Pure
Pure.addedLore: Carved directly from the mysterious rock that hit Gavel 50 years ago, this pure white wand glows with cosmic energy unknown.

Singularity.name: Singularity
Singularity.addedLore: The existence of all things is reflected in the otherworldly jewels of this grand staff, dense enough to have its own gravitational pull. Users have reported their limbs being stretched after usage.

Spring.name: Spring
Spring.addedLore: Arrows fired by this bow are pure ice, but when they hit the enemy, burst into magical water, flash-freezing all that it touches. The frost burns will never heal.

Stratiformis.name: Stratiformis
Stratiformis.addedLore: The Elves managed to harness the power of air itself, forming a bow made entirely of air currents, allowing the user to move swift like the wind, but vulnerable to attacks.

Thrundacrack.name: Thrundacrack
Thrundacrack.addedLore: The raw aspect of thunder, though claimed to be harnessed by a mage in a wand, has only been truly tamed by this mighty blade. Combined electric and life-draining magic intertwine and bring forth the truest, most frightening power of all Thunder.

Warp.name: Warp
Warp.addedLore: The notorious and erratic magical inventor Gawrick once attempted to make teleportation scrolls obsolete, by creating items which would allow the user to phase into an ethereal state to move unhindered. He did not account for the physical ramifications of this process, however.

Weathered.name: Weathered
Weathered.addedLore: A relic of the past in Time Valley was weathered down to a dagger by the sheer power of the wind. When used in battle, mysterious intertwined wind and time magic give it no physical presence.

Maelstrom.name: Maelstrom
Maelstrom.addedLore: Lost by master sailor Carvel in a massive storm, it was carried all the way out to the city of Selchar, where it was found spewing seafoam and lightning bolts.

Maltic's Old Spear.name: Maltic's Old Spear
Maltic's Old Spear.addedLore: This short spear was the first weapon to be produced by the villagers for sale. They are old, but strong.

Mesarock Arch.name: Mesarock Arch
Mesarock Arch.addedLore: The two mesa tribes once were allies until their sacred totems were stolen. Before that time, however, they often shared their talents, and this bow hewn from mesa stone was one such lost craft.

Morrowind.name: Morrowind
Morrowind.addedLore: One of many lost artifacts from the legendary Wind Fortress, the engraving appears to be a cryptic clue to where the Fortress fell. "We shall be found among the dark winds of the morrow."

Olux's Prized Bow.name: Olux's Prized Bow
Olux's Prized Bow.addedLore: This expertly crafted bow was whittled by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its frame was cut from the very toughest tree roots.

Olux's Prized Relik.name: Olux's Prized Relik
Olux's Prized Relik.addedLore: This expertly crafted relik was notched by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its feathers and baubles chime with a soothing melody.

Olux's Prized Dagger.name: Olux's Prized Dagger
Olux's Prized Dagger.addedLore: This expertly crafted dagger was smithed by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It can chop through even the thickest of the swamp's clay with ease.

Olux's Prized Wand.name: Olux's Prized Wand
Olux's Prized Wand.addedLore: This expertly crafted wand was shaped by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shimmers with the purest water from the swamp.

Olux's Prized Spear.name: Olux's Prized Spear
Olux's Prized Spear.addedLore: This expertly crafted spear was forged by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shines brilliantly in even the weakest sunlight.

Narcissist.name: Narcissist
Narcissist.addedLore: The world revolves around you, after all. It's high time you spread the news!

Nemract's Rage.name: Nemract's Rage
Nemract's Rage.addedLore: A year-long monsoon soaked this Nemract-made bow so much, that it has harnessed the very essence of water.

Nepta Floodbringer.name: Nepta Floodbringer
Nepta Floodbringer.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and immense wisdom meld to create a commanding aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for dominion over all.

Ohms' Wish.name: Ohms' Wish
Ohms' Wish.addedLore: "If anyone finds this, leave it at my Gale's gravesite. I promised her a memento, too." This inscription is extremely weathered.

Phoenix Wing.name: Phoenix Wing
Phoenix Wing.addedLore: The magically rejuvenating properties of phoenix ash were imbued into this grand stave in its creator's bid to gain immortality.

Proxima.name: Proxima
Proxima.addedLore: This spear is bright enough that it can cause blindness if you look directly at it. Its immense power is limited by its weight; the weapon is nearly impossible to lift.

Prymari.name: Prymari
Prymari.addedLore: This staff was expertly crafted from fragile spun glass, and tinted with various magical foci that bend light into its most raw components.

Pulsar.name: Pulsar
Pulsar.addedLore: The density of this weapon is almost immeasurable. Despite being light and easy to wield, the spear seems to have its own gravitational pull, slowly dragging enemies closer and making it nearly impossible to put down.

Reaper of Soul.name: Reaper of Soul
Reaper of Soul.addedLore: A grave digger uncovered this blade from the resting place of a notorious pirate that pillaged the islands of the ocean for four decades.

Red Candle.name: Red Candle
Red Candle.addedLore: The flickering flame atop this simple wand is a marvel of magic. It always burns at a comfortable heat, cannot scorch skin even if touched, and never can be snuffed out under any circumstance.

Relic.name: Relic
Relic.addedLore: Despite being proven unrelated, this enigmatic bow was the lynchpin to beginning the great search for the Relics.

Remikas' Righteousness.name: Remikas' Righteousness
Remikas' Righteousness.addedLore: Despite this mace never seeing use by Remikas, it was seen as a symbol of the might of his rule over Gavel. Its true abilities in battle have never been seen.

Reticence.name: Reticence
Reticence.addedLore: Many old mages had to perform lengthy incantations to make potent even their simplest spells. A mage cursed to be mute, however, brought upon a revolution to spellcasting through this simple wand.

Return to Ether.name: Return to Ether
Return to Ether.addedLore: This enigmatic weapon can suddenly blink out of reality with no warning only to appear exactly where it was left later. Artificers have determined that almost the entire bow, by all known laws of nature and magic, should not exist.

Rewind.name: Rewind
Rewind.addedLore: Time moves in strange ways around this translucent blade, speeding and slowing, starting and stopping, with no observable reasoning or pattern.

Rikter.name: Rikter
Rikter.addedLore: Named for an ancient Wynnic word for "Earthquake", this mighty battle hammer causes the very bones of struck enemies to rattle and heave as though the earth itself was splitting under their feet.

Upgraded Archpriest.name: Upgraded Archpriest
Upgraded Archpriest.addedLore: It seems stronger at first glance, but upon closer inspection the blade is rather...soft?

Upgraded Dark Needle.name: Upgraded Dark Needle
Upgraded Dark Needle.addedLore: The magic in this wand seems much weaker than normal...and there's a rather rude message written on the handle.

Upgraded Radiance.name: Upgraded Radiance
Upgraded Radiance.addedLore: The craftsmanship on this bow is rather poor. The paint on the "crystals" is chipping...

Upgraded Steel Buster.name: Upgraded Steel Buster
Upgraded Steel Buster.addedLore: It is significantly heavier than usual...you can't tell if that is good or not, in this case.

Upgraded Whisper.name: Upgraded Whisper
Upgraded Whisper.addedLore: The blade seems sharper than normal, but it also seems rather brittle. The smithing was obviously a hack-job...

Sage.name: Sage
Sage.addedLore: Discipline and experience is channeled into these wands for 10 years in the Bantisu monastery of the canyon, in the hope that they will pass on its teachings to less experienced users.

Scorpion.name: Scorpion
Scorpion.addedLore: This dagger has no blade. Instead, it is layered with the stingers of the Black Shadow Scorpion, which has the ability to vanish entirely from its prey.

Scythe.name: Scythe
Scythe.addedLore: A psychopath claiming herself to be Death incarnate used this dark-bladed scythe on a killing spree that lasted over a year. It reaped hundreds of lives, including her own.

Sitis.name: Sitis
Sitis.addedLore: Wielding it for too long will leave one a dessicated husk, as this dull blade slowly absorbs all liquids around it.

Skin Piercer.name: Skin Piercer
Skin Piercer.addedLore: The average bow can boast a range of skills, but unlike this one, not every bow can penetrate through any organic skin, including dragon hide.

Soundwave.name: Soundwave
Soundwave.addedLore: This bow's thick string fails to shoot arrows effectively, but instead produces low frequency sound waves that erupt from the source in all directions. The sound can implode the eardrums of an enemy with a single strum.

Spiritshock.name: Spiritshock
Spiritshock.addedLore: Potentially one of the most dangerous weapons in existence. A precise enough shot can destroy the soul of those it hits.

StabSand.name: StabSand
StabSand.addedLore: The art of endurance fighting is a skill lost to time. However, a thief that to this day has not been caught, imbued this dagger with the very same ability.

Tachypsychia.name: Tachypsychia
Tachypsychia.addedLore: You will probably irreversibly harm yourself with this, but when has that ever stopped you?

The Berserk.name: The Berserk
The Berserk.addedLore: Forged from unbreakable obsidian eras ago, this heavy hammer has crushed many foes with a single swing.

The Divide.name: The Divide
The Divide.addedLore: Once having held unstoppable amounts of magic, being forced to fuse into one form locked away all but the smallest sliver of their power.

The Exile.name: The Exile
The Exile.addedLore: This indestructible dagger was found floating in the magma of the Molten Heights, with a lament from its exiled smith carved onto the hilt.

Thrunda Ripsaw.name: Thrunda Ripsaw
Thrunda Ripsaw.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and consuming fury combine to create a deadly aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for utter cataclysm.

Thunderbolt.name: Thunderbolt
Thunderbolt.addedLore: This bow has no string. Instead, a thin lightning-like thread is strung upon it. It is said to be limited only by the speed of the user.

Tidebinder.name: Tidebinder
Tidebinder.addedLore: This mysterious, half-liquid trident apparently holds the secret magics to control the ocean's ebb and flow. It is incapable of touching solid ground.

Tisaun's Proof.name: Tisaun's Proof
Tisaun's Proof.addedLore: The wear upon this broken old battle spear does not affect its ability in battle. The souls of a thousand fallen warriors resound within it.

Toaster.name: Toaster
Toaster.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] This peculiar weapon was once wielded by the firey warrior Igbar, who used it to great effect in nether-endurance competitions.

Torrential Tide.name: Torrential Tide
Torrential Tide.addedLore: The tides of the ocean, once bound, became useful magic power sources. They were once utilized for weapons, but to harness the unstable force of the raging sea was considered too dangerous.

Waves Raiser.name: Waves Raiser
Waves Raiser.addedLore: The mystery of the ocean’s appearance has eluded scholars for centuries. It is believed that many years ago, warlocks used wands like this one in an attempt to submerge the world.

Zephra Shredder.name: Zephra Shredder
Zephra Shredder.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and sheer rage intertwine to create a fearsome sight, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for total destruction.

Zero.name: Zero
Zero.addedLore: The unstable power within this bow is capable of great destruction, but seems to zero out at the most crucial moments in battle. Only the most skillful archers can wield this weapon with confidence.

default.name: default
default.addedLore: This is a rad weapon yo. Let's make the lore longer so we can test how long it can go. Hi Jumla!
